---
// Short read: P2P vs P2M crossover. Data: public/data/economy/reads/shops-vs-people.json
// (scripts/build-reads-data.mjs). Read at build for the figures; embedded for the chart.
import ReadLayout from '../../../components/read/ReadLayout.astro';
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

const data = JSON.parse(readFileSync(fileURLToPath(new URL('../../../../public/data/economy/reads/shops-vs-people.json', import.meta.url)), 'utf8'));
const { stats } = data;
const inr = (n: number) => '₹' + n.toLocaleString('en-IN');
const payload = JSON.stringify(data);
---

<ReadLayout
  slug="shops-vs-people"
  kicker="Economy · Monthly"
  asOf={stats.asOf}
>
  <figure class="chartfig">
    <div class="chart" id="read-chart" style="height:360px"></div>
    <figcaption>Share of UPI payments by count: <span class="e e-merch">merchant</span> vs <span class="e e-p2p">person-to-person</span>, monthly. Source: NPCI.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>When UPI took off it was mostly people paying people: rent to a landlord, a share of dinner to
      a friend. That flipped in <strong>{stats.crossover}</strong>. Since then most UPI payments have
      gone to <span class="e e-merch">merchants</span> rather than <span class="e e-p2p">people</span>,
      and the gap has only widened. Today about <strong>{stats.volPctM}%</strong> of UPI payments by
      count go to shops. And that understates it: a small seller who takes payment on a personal
      account is not counted as a merchant here, so the true share going to commerce is higher still.</p>
    <p>The reason is the QR code. A sticker on a tea stall or a vegetable cart turned every small
      purchase into a UPI payment, and small purchases are frequent. The average
      <span class="e e-merch">merchant</span> payment is tiny, about <strong>{inr(stats.ticketP2M)}</strong>,
      against <strong>{inr(stats.ticketP2P)}</strong> for a <span class="e e-p2p">person-to-person</span>
      transfer. Counted one tap at a time, the chaiwallah now outweighs the landlord.</p>

    <div class="pullstat">
      <div><span class="n e-merch">{stats.volPctM}%</span><span class="l">of UPI <em>payments</em> go to merchants</span></div>
      <div><span class="n e-p2p">{100 - stats.valPctM}%</span><span class="l">of the <em>money</em> still moves between people</span></div>
    </div>

    <p>By value, though, person-to-person still wins. Such transfers are so much larger that even as
      <span class="e e-merch">merchants</span> take {stats.volPctM}% of the volume, they account for
      only about <strong>{stats.valPctM}%</strong> of the money. UPI is really two systems wearing one
      logo: a high-frequency tap for buying things, and a heavier pipe for moving money between people.</p>

    <p class="source">Source: NPCI UPI P2P/P2M statistics, processed by Time Series of India.
      <a href="/economy/explore/payments">Explore the dashboard →</a></p>
  </div>

  <script type="application/json" id="read-data" set:html={payload}></script>
</ReadLayout>

<script>
  import * as echarts from 'echarts';
  import { buildPanel, readTokens } from '../../../lib/dashboards/runtime';
  import type { PanelSpec, CtrlState } from '../../../lib/dashboards/runtime';

  const data = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('read-data')!.textContent!);
  const host = document.getElementById('read-chart');
  if (host) {
    const spec: PanelSpec = { id: 'p2m', title: '', chart: 'line', staticAxis: true, encoding: { x: 'date', series: 'kind', y: 'share_pct' } };
    const opt = () => {
      const t = readTokens();
      const o: any = buildPanel(spec, data.shareRows, { metric: 'volume_cr' } as CtrlState, t);
      const col: Record<string, string> = { Merchant: t.palette[0], 'Person-to-person': t.palette[1] };
      o.series = o.series.map((s: any) => ({ ...s, lineStyle: { ...s.lineStyle, color: col[s.name] }, itemStyle: { ...s.itemStyle, color: col[s.name] } }));
      o.series[0] = { ...o.series[0], markLine: { silent: true, symbol: 'none', data: [{ xAxis: data.stats.crossDate }], lineStyle: { color: t.subtle, type: 'dashed' }, label: { formatter: 'Aug 22', color: t.subtle, fontFamily: t.mono, fontSize: 10 } } };
      return o;
    };
    const chart = echarts.init(host);
    const render = () => chart.setOption(opt(), true);
    new ResizeObserver(() => chart.resize()).observe(host);
    new MutationObserver(render).observe(document.documentElement, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-theme', 'data-units'] });
    render();
    document.fonts?.ready.then(render);
  }
</script>
